column5: WELL I FIGURED I BETTER GO OUT AND GET SOME CHROME IN BEFORE I HEAD OFF TO NIPPISING ON FRI!! BEAUTY SUNNY MORN BUT TURNED UGLY IN THE AFT!!! WAS SLOW AND WATERS WERE PRETTY DIRTY STILL(ABOUT 4"VIS) MANAGED TO GO 2 FOR 6!! WINTER HAS REALLY SET IN ON THE FISH!!!HARDLY ANY FIGHT TO THEM AT ALL!! NORMAL FOR THIS TIME OF YR WHEN THE METABALISM SLOWS DOWN!!!

Wow!! Nice work Scott!  I gotta get myself back there and catch some more.  Time is hard to find right now though.  Wish I had the winter off as well...if I did, then you'd have a regular fishing partner!! lol
Nice chromers CC   Good luck at the big N
Hey CC, at least you got out fishing. Nothing wrong with that bow either. Looks like a real beauty.
VERY NICE FISH SCOTT,KEEP UP THE GREAT FISHIN MAN...CHEERS
Knew you would recover quickly from that skunk!  Great looking fish, thanks for sharing, can't wait to read your next post     bly
You fishin off a pier CC? How far out is it froze up?  nice lookin fish!
TX ALL!!! KEMP SOME PIERS ARE FROZEN AND ALOT OF OTHERS ARE OPEN!!! DIFFERENT EVERYDAY SINCE WIND CAN BLOW IT ALL BACK IN  LOL

CC don't use up all the luck before the weekend buddy. I'm counting on some of that for the trip north. H*ll getting away from the GTA and work is good enough. Maybe thats my problem, going on a fishing trip and not catching a fish doesn't bother me. I gotta set my goals higher!  Chris.
So that is what a rainbow looks like .lol I have never caught one
nice chunky fish, good luck on your trip...
Nice nice. W2G. i bet u were pretty cold out there today.     jordan
Glad to see they are not totally lockjawed! Nice job man... Keep on bringing these great reports
